# ~/.p10k.zsh — Powerlevel10k user prompt config.
# REPLACE ME with your real `p10k configure`-generated file. chezmoi will
# manage it like any other dotfile; once you drop your real config here and
# commit, every machine running `chezmoi update` picks up the same prompt.
#
# Until then, this empty file lets p10k fall back to its default prompt
# without error. You can also regenerate the config any time with:
#     p10k configure
# and then `chezmoi re-add ~/.p10k.zsh` to capture the result.
